Thiru:

Sounds like something has been broken.  If you set JMX=false, then 
Heritrix just keeps a simple hash map of all running instances rather 
than house the list of instances in a JMX Agent.   Try setting 
JMX=true.  IIRC in tomcat at least, its harmless though not as reachable 
as registering with the JVM&#39;s JMX Agent as heritrix normally does.  Also 
add logging in around the registration and deregistration of instances 
to figure why the new instance is not being added to the hash of 
instances and so is not findable by the UI (&quot;No instance or Multiple 
instances&#39; error).

St.Ack


