Thiru:&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
Sounds like something has been broken.&nbsp; If you set JMX=false, then
Heritrix just keeps a simple hash map of all running instances rather
than house the list of instances in a JMX Agent.&nbsp;&nbsp; Try setting
JMX=true.&nbsp; IIRC in tomcat at least, its harmless though not as
reachable as registering with the JVM&#39;s JMX Agent as heritrix normally
does.&nbsp; Also add logging in around the registration and deregistration
of instances to figure why the new instance is not being added to the
hash of instances and so is not findable by the UI (&quot;No instance or
Multiple instances&#39; error).&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
St.Ack&lt;br&gt;
&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
